Arcata, Humboldt County, California
recordings.rmk:
This 13-second recording documents two song bouts of an adult male Chestnut-sided Warbler. This particular male was quite aggressive toward other small passerines. It would chase American Goldfinches and House Finches. In one instance, it was seen chest-butting a male American Goldfinch. But in this recording it was not displaying any aggression. This species is a low-density visitor to California.

This recording was made with an iPhone 5s with stock microphone and Røde Rec application. This recording has not been modified or edited.

Additional details regarding context may be found at: http://ebird.org/ebird/view/checklist?subID=S23932255
